docs.abstract: A new version of the teen drama arrives Thursday on HBO Max, still glamorous but also reflective of changed attitudes toward wealth and privilege.
docs.snippet: A new version of the teen drama arrives Thursday on HBO Max, still glamorous but also reflective of changed attitudes toward wealth and privilege.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a sultry June morning, a small battalion of camera operators, production assistants, and hair and makeup pros descended on a subway entrance on the Upper West Side of Manhattan. An assistant director barked a command and suddenly the ordinary commuters vanished, replaced by glam pedestrians attired in kicky fall fashion. Shoes gleamed, teeth glinted, each ponytail and pompadour shone. In an instant, a traffic median had transformed into a sweat-free space of sparkle, scandal, possibility. Spotted at 72nd and Broadway: “Gossip Girl,” back again. XOXO.

headline.main: New York, ‘Gossip Girl’ Loves You, Again

docs.abstract: The giddy anticipation that real change might happen on the island is tempered by wariness, especially from older exiles, that this might be one more disappointment.
docs.snippet: The giddy anticipation that real change might happen on the island is tempered by wariness, especially from older exiles, that this might be one more disappointment.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIAMI — The moment that Cuban exiles in Florida have so fervently ached for over the past six decades did not come when the Soviet Union fell in 1991 or when Fidel Castro died in 2016. It arrived, to their surprise, last Sunday, when Cubans on the island rushed the streets to denounce a Communist government that has left them oppressed, sick and hungry.

headline.main: Miami Embraces Cuba Protests: ‘I Never Thought That This Day Would Come’
headline.print_headline: Miami Embraces Protest Over Cuba, And Hopes Real Change Will Come

docs.abstract: Five years ago, players were fined for wearing unapproved shirts to protest the fatal shootings of two Black men. The league has since embraced players’ desire to speak out against social injustice.
docs.snippet: Five years ago, players were fined for wearing unapproved shirts to protest the fatal shootings of two Black men. The league has since embraced players’ desire to speak out against social injustice.
docs.lead_paragraph: On June 22, the Liberty hosted a game celebrating Juneteenth. Some players wore Black Lives Matter T-shirts during shootaround, and the night’s festivities began with a rendition of “Lift Every Voice and Sing,” often considered the national anthem of Black Americans.

headline.main: The Liberty’s Role in Making W.N.B.A. Players ‘Top Dogs’ of Activism
headline.print_headline: The Liberty Pushed for Social Justice Back When It Got Them Fined
